      <hedline>
        <hl1>EARNINGS DROP AT BRITISH TELECOM</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Alan Cowell</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cowell, Alan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>British Telecommunications PLC says earnings dropped 42 percent in quarter ended June 30, to 314 million pounds, or $476 million, from 546 million pounds a year earlier; says net debt doubled to 15.4 billion pounds, or $23.2 billion (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Borrowing for expansion and the cost of a new wireless license contributed to a 42 percent drop in quarterly earnings at British Telecommunications P.L.C., to $:314 million, or $476 million, from $:546 million a year earlier. British Telecommunications said its net debt almost doubled in the quarter, which ended on June 30, to 15.4 [pounds] billion, or $23.2 billion.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell (NYT)</p>
      </block>
